  145. ‌let reset() =
  146.   (* When reset() is called for the first time, the current stamp reflects
  147.      all hard pseudo-registers that have been allocated by Proc, so
  148.      remember it and use it as the base stamp for allocating
  149.      soft pseudo-registers *)
  150.   if !first_virtual_reg_stamp = -1 then begin
  151.     first_virtual_reg_stamp := !currstamp;
  152.     assert (!reg_list = []) (* Only hard regs created before now *)
  153.   end;
  154.   currstamp := !first_virtual_reg_stamp;
  155.   reg_list := [];
  156.   visit_generation := 1;
  157.   !hw_reg_list |> List.iter (fun r ->
  158.     r.visited <- unvisited)

  160. let all_registers() = !reg_list
  161. let num_registers() = !currstamp

  163. let reinit_reg r =
  164.   r.loc <- Unknown;
  165.   r.interf <- [];
  166.   r.prefer <- [];
  167.   r.degree <- 0;
  168.   (* Preserve the very high spill costs introduced by the reloading pass *)
  169.   if r.spill_cost >= 100000
  170.   then r.spill_cost <- 100000
  171.   else r.spill_cost <- 0

  173. let reinit() =
  174.   List.iter reinit_reg !reg_list

  185. let add_set_array s v =
  186.   match Array.length v with
  187.     0 -> s
  188.   | 1 -> Set.add v.(0) s
  189.   | n -> let rec add_all i =
  190.            if i >= n then s else Set.add v.(i) (add_all(i+1))
  191.          in add_all 0
